	   <tr><td colspan=2>All I gotz to say (besides speaking in ebonics, no ratial slur or insult, just like speaking it)is that out of all the classes that I've played, mages are the most FUN!!!  Sure, I'm not a high level enchanter than can mes everything between here and rivervale (I WOULD like to make a slur or 20 toward the halfling npc's there), but you have pets (fire all the way), you have dd spells that hit HARD, you have nice area effect spells (remember, cast from a distance), and you can pull almost anything out your wazoo (weapons, items, food, etc).  We get the best of almost all worlds (when we get SoW, then we'll be gods).  Now I am far from being THE authority on Everquest, mages, or anything else for that matter, but in my yearish (little more) of playing I've come to find, DO NOT GET A CHARACTER THAT REQUIRES YOU TO SOLO FIRST.  I started with a cleric, warrior, went to alot of different others (I've been every class, and almost every race, cept for halfling or highelf) and this helped me appreciate not having to run around every time I logged in for 20+ minutes, (fill in level and class) LOOKING FOR GROUP, and when the group dies, sure enough, YOU WILL DIE.  It helps me appreciate things more.  Also pets, sure, I read someone said we're nothing without them.  He may be right, but I can sure as hell outlevel him/her without batting an eye if he/she is a mele-based class.  So there.  Next, everyone is asking, WHERE DO I GO TO LEVEL, WHERE DO I DO THIS, WHERE DO I GET THAT.  As Everquest goes on, I've learned that, if you can, try to find things out on your own, so much more fun, now, suggestions and asking questions are ALWAYS GOOD (lord knows it has helped me) but you need to explore, do, have fun, hell, walk up to a halfling and make for conversation (expecially if they give you a gossimer robe, nicest thing one has ever done).  Now, as for pets, use whatever tickles your fancy and doesn't get you killed, feeling like dirt, earth pet, angry, fire pet, etc.  There really isn't a good or bad pet, some are more troublesome and pop more than others, but they all do the same thing, attack until death or until told not too.  Besides that, spells, yakety schmackety, same ole stuff.  Summons, heh, those are REAL fun, and you save money, your hungry, make food, thirsty, make water, (wish you could make redwine), but that's another story *swig*.  Anyways, play hard, make friends, level, camp, do everything in eq that you can (cept for kill Captain N'Farre, my personal hero, who is, the man) And who knows, I might make another post (super huge) on every class, race, goodpoints and bad about them, etc.  Hell, why not now.  HAHAHAHAHAHA.<br><br>Good fight, Good night.<br><br>Dashiatis<br><br>Bristlebane<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
