	   <tr><td colspan=2>Okay, first off to answer the fella asking about where to go at lvl 4. Frankly, the world of Norrath is huge and there are lots of mobs for you at lower levels. You can stay in Gfay or head to BB or whatever, it's your preference. Just make sure you can find a guard to run to if you get overrun. <br><br>Next, I wanted to answer the fella who says that if your pet gets killed, we need to go in and melee for a bit, you are obviously thinking of lower level magicians. I'm lvl 49 and I'll tell you that if I tried to stand toe-to-toe with a mob, even a greenie, I would be taking a dirt nap very quickly. Although there are those who swear that they will always try to melee a mob alongside their pet, I am one who has stopped using a weapon since lvl 24 or so. Simply, the mobs hit too hard and we have too few HP. Also, if I actually did try to melee, the most I would do is about 30 dmg. For those who still insist on dancing with high level mobs, get ready to see this message alot:<br><br>LOADING, PLEASE WAIT...<br>You have lost a level!<br><br>49 Magi<br>Karana server<br><br><br> <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
